<refnamediv><refname>impsnr</refname><refpurpose>Compute peak signal-to-noise ratio between two images.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>value = impsnr(im1, im2)
value = impsnr(im1, im2, peak)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>im1, im2</term><listitem><para>Images with matching sizes.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>peak</term><listitem><para>Peak signal value. Default is inferred from the input type and value range.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>value</term><listitem><para>Peak signal-to-noise ratio in dB.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>impsnr</function> reports PSNR in dB using <function>immse</function>.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
im = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/" + "baboon.png"));
value = impsnr(im, im);
]]></programlisting></refsection>
